# work-strategy minds — granular use (no default tri-frame)

Do **not** assume **tri-frame** (Mercouris + Mearsheimer + Barnes together) on every **`strategy`**, **`strategy pass`**, **`work-strategy`**, or generic **skill-strategy** / strategy-notebook pass.

**Default:** Use **zero, one, two, or three** lenses as the operator indicates — or **none** (plain Signal / Judgment / Links without M/M/B labeling). Single-lens and two-lens passes are normal.

**Apply tri-frame or strict LEARN MODE** only when the operator explicitly asks (e.g. **tri-frame**, **LEARN MODE**, **all three minds**, or equivalent). Full **LEARN MODE** protocol (ordering, extraction, SCHOLAR hooks) remains in [`docs/skill-work/work-strategy/LEARN_MODE_RULES.md`](../../docs/skill-work/work-strategy/LEARN_MODE_RULES.md) for those sessions.

**Entry points:** [`docs/skill-work/work-strategy/minds/README.md`](../../docs/skill-work/work-strategy/minds/README.md) → canonical **`strategy-notebook/minds/CIV-MIND-*.md`** (full mind bodies in-repo; **no civ-mem required**). Optional upstream diff: `research/repos/civilization_memory/docs/templates/CIV–MIND–*.md` when present.
